[0.618, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[0.229, "o", "2026-06-07 12:25:57 0 [Warning] Can't create test file '/usr/--max_allowed_packet=8M/ramzimaysan.lower-test' (Errcode: 2 \"No such file or directory\")\r\n\u0007/usr/bin/mariadbd: Can't change dir to '/usr/--max_allowed_packet=8M/' (Errcode: 2 \"No such file or directory\")\r\n2026-06-07 12:25:57 0 [ERROR] Aborting\r\n"]
[0.018, "o", "\r\nInstallation of system tables failed!  Examine the logs in\r\n./data for more information.\r\n\r\nThe problem could be conflicting information in an external\r\nmy.cnf files. You can ignore these by doing:\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    shell> /usr/bin/mariadb-install-db --defaults-file=~/.my.cnf\r\n\r\nYou can also try to start the mariadbd daemon with:\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    shell> /usr/bin/mariadbd --skip-grant-tables --general-log &\r\n\r\nand use the command line tool /usr/bin/mariadb\r\nto connect to the mysql database and look at the grant tables:\r\n\r\n    shell> /usr/bin/mariadb -u root mysql\r\n    MariaDB> show tables;\r\n\r\nTry '/usr/bin/mariadbd --help' if you have problems with paths.  Using\r\n--general-log gives you a log in ./data that may be helpful.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\nThe latest information about mariadb-install-db is available at\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-system-tables-mysql_install_db\r\nYou can find the latest source at https://downloads.mariadb.org and\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "the MariaDB discuss email list at https://lists.mariadb.org/postorius/lists/discuss.lists.mariadb.org/\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\nPlease check all of the above before submitting a bug report\r\nat https://mariadb.org/jira\r\n\r\n"]
