[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-A\u001b[m\u000f Set Mark     \u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-]\u001b[m\u000f To Bracket   \u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-B\u001b[m\u000f Previous\u001b[48;2H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fX\u001b[m\u000f Exit  \u001b[48;18H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^R\u001b[m\u000f Read File     \u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^\\\u001b[m\u000f Replace       \u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^U\u001b[m\u000f Paste\u001b[48;70H"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fJ\u001b[m\u000f Justify\u001b[86G\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^/\u001b[m\u000f Go To Line    \u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-E\u001b[m\u000f Redo\u001b[48;120H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-6\u001b[m\u000f Copy\u001b[48;137H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^B\u001b[m\u000f Where Was     \u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-F\u001b[m\u000f Next"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\u001b[2d; of the INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an expression\r\u001b[3d; (e.g. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string (\"bar\"), or a reference to a\r\u001b[4d;"]
[0.000, "o", " previously set variable or directive (e.g. ${foo})\r\u001b[5d"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[6d; Expressions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parentheses:\u001b[7;3H|  bitwise OR\u001b[K\u001b[8;3H^  bitwise XOR\u001b[K\r\u001b[9d; &  bitwise AND\u001b[10;3H~  bitwise NOT\u001b[K\u001b[11;3H!  boolean NOT\u001b[K\r\u001b[12d\u001b[K\u001b[13d; Boolean flags can be turned on using the values 1, On, True or Yes.\u001b[14;3HThey can be turned off using the values 0, Off, False or No.\r\u001b[15d\u001b[K\u001b[16d; An empty string can be denoted by simply not writing anything after the equal\u001b[17;3Hsign, or by using the None keyword:\r\u001b[18d\u001b[K\u001b[19d; foo =         ; sets foo to an empty string\u001b[20;3Hfoo = None    ; sets foo to an empty string\u001b[K\u001b[21;3Hfoo = \"None\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None'\u001b[23;3HIf you use constants in your value, and these constants belong to a\u001b[24;3Hdynamically loaded \u001b[30m\u001b[43mextension\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f (either a PHP extension or a Zend extension),\u001b[25;3Hyou may only use these constants *after* the line that loads the extension.\r\u001b[26d\u001b[K\u001b[27d;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[28;3HAbout this file ;\u001b[K\r\u001b[29d;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\u001b[30;3HPHP comes packaged with two INI files. One that is recommended to be used\u001b[31;3Hin production environments and one that is recommended to be used in\u001b[32;3Hdevelopment environments.\u001b[K\r\u001b[33d"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[34d; php.ini-production contains settings which hold security, performance and\u001b[35;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "best practices at its core. But please be aware, these settings may break\r\u001b[36d; compatibility with older or less security-conscious applications. We\u001b[37;3Hrecommending using the production ini in production and testing environments.\r\u001b[38d"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[39d; "]
[0.000, "o", "php.ini-development is very similar to its production variant, except it is\u001b[40;3Hmuch more verbose when it comes to errors. We recommend using the\u001b[41;3Hdevelopment version only in development environments, as errors shown to\u001b[42;3Happlication users can inadvertently leak otherwise secure information.\u001b[K\u001b[44;5His is the php.ini-production INI file.\u001b[K\r\u001b[45d\u001b[K\u001b[24;22H"]
