d| EXPLANATION OF VARIABLES\r\u001b[16d| -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\u001b[17d|\u001b[18d\b|\u001b[9G['dsn']\u001b[22GThe full DSN string describe a connection to the database.\r\u001b[19d|\u001b[9G['hostname'] The hostname of your database server.\r\u001b[20d|\u001b[9G['username'] The username used to connect to the database\r\u001b[21d|\u001b[9G['password'] The password used to connect to the database\r\u001b[22d|\u001b[9G['database'] The name of the database you want to connect to\r\u001b[23d|\u001b[9G['dbdriver'] The database driver. e.g.: mysqli.\r\u001b[24d|\u001b[24;25HCurrently supported:\r\u001b[25d|\u001b[25;34Hcubrid, ibase, mssql, mysql, mysqli, oci8,\r\u001b[26d|\u001b[26;34Hodbc, pdo, postgre, sqlite, sqlite3, sqlsrv\r\u001b[27d|\u001b[9G['dbprefix'] You can add an optional prefix, which will be added\r\u001b[28d|\u001b[28;34Hto the table name when using the  Query Builder class\r\u001b[29d|\u001b[9G['pconnect'] TRUE/FALSE - Whether to use a persistent connection\r\u001b[30d|\u001b[9G['db_debug'] TRUE/FALSE - Whether database errors should be displayed.\r\u001b[31d|\u001b[9G['cache_on'] TRUE/FALSE - Enables/disables query caching\r\u001b[32d|\u001b[9G['cachedir'] The path to the folder where cache files should be stored\r\u001b[33d|\u001b[9G['char_set'] The character set used in communicating with the database\r\u001b[34d|\u001b[9G['dbcollat'] The character collation used in communicating with the database\r\u001b[35d|\u001b[35;34HNOTE: For MySQL and MySQLi databases, this setting is only used\r\u001b[36d|\u001b[36;34Has a backup if your server is running PHP < 5.2.3 or MySQL < 5.0.7\r\u001b[37d|\u001b[37;34H(and in table creation queries made with DB Forge).\r\u001b[38d|\u001b[38;34HThere is an incompatibility in PHP with mysql_real_escape_string() which\r\u001b[39d|\u001b[39;34Hcan make your site vulnerable to SQL injection if you are using a\r\u001b[40d|\u001b[40;34Hmulti-byte character set and are running versions lower than these.\r\u001b[41d|\u001b[41;34HSites using Latin-1 or UTF-8 database character set and collation are unaffected.\r\u001b[42d|\u001b[9G['swap_pre'] A default table prefix that should be swapped with the dbprefix\r\u001b[43d|\u001b[9G['encrypt']  Whether or not to use an encrypted connection.\r\u001b[44d|\u001b[45d\b|\u001b[45;25H'mysql' (deprecated), 'sqlsrv' and 'pdo/sqlsrv' drivers accept TRUE/FALSE\r\u001b[2d\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
